 of juridical power, the relation between humans and animals, and finally messianism and the politics to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aDeconstruction. 4aBiopolitics. 4aContinental Philosophy. 4aCritical Theory. 4aDeconstruction. 4aFrench Philosophy. 4aGiorgio Agamben. 4aItalian philosophy. 4aJacques Derrida. 4aPhilosophy. 4acontemporary philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071187540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823262076zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823262076423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823262076.jpg  a978-3-11-071187-5  NYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK